spell.Description:
Animate up to 10 objects. Medium count as two objects, large count as four, huge count as eight.
    You can't animate something larger than huge. Each becomes a creature under your control until the spell ends or they are destroyed.
    As a bonus action you can command any creature made with this spell within 500 ft (if you control multiple creatures you can command any and all of them at once).
    You decide what action the creature will take and where it will move or you can issue a more general command such as guarding a particular chamber.
    If you issue no commands, the creature only defends it self against hostile creatures.
    Once given the creature contiues to follow the order until completion.
    Animated creature statistics:
    Tiny: 20hp; 18 AC; +8 to hit; 1d4+4 damage; 4 str; 18 dex;
    Small: 25hp; 16 AC; +4 to hit; 1d8+2 damage; 6 str; 14 dex;
    Medium: 40hp; 13 AC; +5 to hit; 2d6+1 damage; 10 str; 12 dex;
    Large: 50hp; 10 AC; +6 to hit; 2d10+2 damage; 14 str; 10 dex;
    Huge: 80hp; 10 AC; +8 to hit; 2d12+4 damage; 18 str; 6 dex;
    Animated objects have 10 constitution, 3 intelligence and wisdom, and 1 charisma.
    Their movement speed is 30. If the object lacks legs it has a fly speed of 30 and can hover.
    Objects commanded to attack make a single melee attack against a creature within 5 feet of it. It makes a slam attack and deals bludgeoning damage.
    At higher levels. If you cast this spell using a higher level spell slot, it can animate two additional objects for each slot above 5th.
